      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MY ULTIMATE BUDDHA (5) was good in his first outing since switching from Queensland and joining Josh Farrugia, coming from the back row for a 1.7m second at this circuit and distance last week. Won the only other time he raced here. Leading hope. TIGERLICIOUS (8) put the writing on the wall with back-to-back seconds before coming from a similar draw to this and delivering at the latest appearance, scoring by 5 metres at this circuit and distance. Going well and could strike again. LOUISE LUCK (1) kicked off for Seaton Grima with a Menangle win before chasing TIGERLICIOUS as runner-up last week. Both of those results were from much wider barriers so she looks well served by the inside draw. LEAVE IT TO LUCY (2) returns to the front row and won the last time she started from there.",
